Sex check was performed using heterozygosity rate of sex chromosomes and by examining the coverage of sex chromosomes. This identified a sex mismatch when the reported sex does not match the biological sex and chromosomal abnormality when extra chromosomes were present. Relatedness testing and principal component analysis (PCA) were done following established pipelines using eligible bi-allelic autosomal SNPs using PLINK (v1.9). Of all bi-allelic autosomal SNPs, we removed variants that had minor allele frequency < 0.05, missing rate per variant >0.01, missing rate per variant in cases and controls >0.02 or P < 0.005, Hardy–Weinberg equilibrium false discovery rate (FDR) < 1×10−6 (controls) or <1×10−10 (cases), or were in linkage disequilibrium (r2 > 0.05). Relatedness testing identified any pairs of subjects with \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
